text: The 1992 Country Music Association Awards, 26th Ceremony, was held on September 30, 1992 at the Grand Ole Opry House, Nashville, Tennessee, and was hosted by CMA Award Winners, Vince Gill and Reba McEntire. == Winners and Nominees == Winner are in Bold. {| class="wikitable" ! style="background:#EEDD85; width=50%" |Entertainer of the Year ! style="background:#EEDD85; width=50%" |Album of the Year |- | valign="top" | * Garth Brooks **Vince Gill **Alan Jackson **Reba McEntire **Travis Tritt | valign="top" | * Ropin' the Wind - Garth Brooks ** Brand New Man - Brooks & Dunn ** For My Broken Heart - Reba McEntire ** What Do I Do with Me - Tanya Tucker ** Wynonna - Wynonna |- ! style="background:#EEDD82; width=50%" |Male Vocalist of the Year ! style="background:#EEDD82; width=50%" |Female Vocalist of the Year |- | valign="top" | * Vince Gill **Garth Brooks **Joe Diffie **Alan Jackson **Travis Tritt | valign="top" | * Mary Chapin Carpenter ** Reba McEntire ** Tanya Tucker ** Trisha Yearwood ** Wynonna |- ! style="background:#EEDD82; width=50%" |Vocal Group of the Year ! style="background:#EEDD82; width=50%" |Vocal Duo of the Year |- | valign="top" | * Diamond Rio ** Alabama ** McBride & The Ride ** Sawyer Brown ** Shenandoah | valign="top" | * Brooks & Dunn ** Baillie & The Boys ** Bellamy Brothers ** The Judds ** Sweetheart of the Rodeo |- ! style="background:#EEDD82; width=50%" |Single of the Year ! style="background:#EEDD82; width=50%" |Song of the Year |- | valign="top" | * "Achy Breaky Heart" - Billy Ray Cyrus **"I Feel Lucky" - Mary Chapin Carpenter ** "Look at Us" - Vince Gill ** "Love, Me" - Collin Raye ** "Maybe It Was Memphis" - Pam Tillis | valign="top" | * "Look at Us" - Vince Gill and Max D.
